OL,6,FPolice watchdog the Independent Office
OL,7,Ffor Police Conduct (IOPC) investigated
OL,8,FJones over accusations he had started
OL,9,Frelationships with two women he met
OL,10,Fthrough his policing duties. He was
OL,11,Falso accused of misleading his
OL,12,Fsupervisor and the professional
OL,13,Fstandards department over the nature
OL,14,Fof one of his relationships.
OL,16,FIt found that the then-DC formed
OL,17,Frelationships in 2017 and 2019 whIle
OL,18,Fbeing the officer responsible for
OL,19,Finvestigating two separate criminal
OL,20,Fcases.
