OL,4,Cwith women he met on the job
OL,6,F"Regardless of whether either woman at
OL,7,Fthe time saw themselves as vulnerable,
OL,8,Fboth of them had turned to the police
OL,9,Ffor help. Any police officer should
OL,10,Frecognise it would be wholly wrong to
OL,11,Fseek any personal relationship with a
OL,12,Fmember of the public in such
OL,13,Fcircumstances, especially while
OL,14,Fconducting a criminal investigation
OL,15,Frelating directly to that person or
OL,16,Ftheir family.
OL,18,F"Former DC Jones was an officer with
OL,19,Fmore than 20 years' experience and it
OL,20,Fis abundantly clear he knew what he
OL,21,Fwas doing was wrong.
