OL,6,F"He continued the relationships over a
OL,7,Fperiod of years. Through his training,
OL,8,Fpolicing roles and the clear guidance
OL,9,Fon maintaining professional boundaries
OL,10,Fpolice officers receive, he must have
OL,11,Fknown his behaviour was wrong.
OL,13,F"The public expect police officers to
OL,14,Fprotect them; that is their role. When
OL,15,Fthis role is compromised by officers
OL,16,For staff who abuse their position for
OL,17,Fa sexual purpose then this behaviour
OL,18,Famounts to serious corruption."
OL,20,FDC Jones retired from the force in
